Alright — let’s do this properly and practically for your setup 👍
You’re on Ubuntu 24.04 + disconnected environment, so normal apt install won’t work.


---

🧩 What you’re trying to install

You need the CLI:

nmstatectl
(from the NMState project)


👉 This is only required for validation on bastion, not for the cluster itself.


---

✅ Method 1 — Recommended (Virtual Environment)

This works cleanly on Ubuntu 24.04.


---

🔧 Step 1: Install venv support (if DNS works)

sudo apt install -y python3-venv

👉 If DNS is broken, skip this and go to Method 2


---

🔧 Step 2: Create virtual environment

python3 -m venv nmstate-venv


---

🔧 Step 3: Activate

source nmstate-venv/bin/activate


---

🔧 Step 4: Install nmstate

pip install nmstate


---

🔧 Step 5: Verify

nmstatectl --version


---

🔧 Step 6: Export path (IMPORTANT)

export PATH=$PWD/nmstate-venv/bin:$PATH


---

🔁 Now retry OpenShift command

./openshift-install agent create cluster-manifests


---

❌ But your case = DISCONNECTED

Your logs show:

Temporary failure resolving archive.ubuntu.com

👉 So pip also won’t work online.


---

✅ Method 2 — Offline Installation (Best for you)

💻 On a machine with internet:

pip3 download nmstate

This downloads:

.whl files



---

📦 Copy to bastion

Use scp / USB:

scp *.whl sno7@haproxy:~/nmstate/


---

🔧 On bastion:

cd ~/nmstate
python3 -m venv nmstate-venv
source nmstate-venv/bin/activate
pip install *.whl


---

✅ Verify

nmstatectl --version


---

⚡ Method 3 — Quick Force Install (not recommended)

sudo pip3 install nmstate --break-system-packages

👉 Works fast
⚠️ Can break system Python


---

🚀 Method 4 — Skip Installation (MOST USED in labs)

Since you're doing:

SNO

Agent-based

Disconnected


👉 You can skip nmstate completely:

export NMSTATECTL_PATH=/bin/true

Then:

./openshift-install agent create cluster-manifests


---

🧠 What I recommend for YOU

Given your setup:

👉 Best option:

Use Method 4 (skip validation)
✔ Fast
✔ No internet needed
✔ Widely used in disconnected labs



